X
\;\tau \circ X = \sigma,\;
\tau = \begin{bmatrix}  1 & 2 & 3 & 4 & 5\\ 3 & 4 & 5 & 2 & 1  \end{bmatrix} = (1,3,5)(2,4)
\sigma = \begin{bmatrix}  1 & 2 & 3 & 4 & 5\\ 3 & 2 & 1 & 5 & 4  \end{bmatrix} = (1,3)(2)(4,5)
X
\tau
\tau^{-1}
X
\tau = \begin{bmatrix}  1 & 2 & 3 & 4 & 5\\ 3 & 4 & 5 & 2 & 1  \end{bmatrix} = (1,3,5)(2,4)
X = \begin{bmatrix}  3 & 4 & 5 & 2 & 1\\ 3 & 2 & 1 & 5 & 4  \end{bmatrix} = (1,4,2,5)(3)
\sigma = \begin{bmatrix}  1 & 2 & 3 & 4 & 5\\ 3 & 2 & 1 & 5 & 4  \end{bmatrix} = (1,3)(2)(4,5)
\tau \circ X = \sigma \implies X=\tau^{-1}\sigma
\tau^{-1}
\tau^{-1}=[(1,3,5)(2,4)]^{-1}=[(2,4)^{-1}][(1,3,5)^{-1}]=(2,4)(1,5,3)
X=(2,4)(1,3,5)(1,3)(4,5)
